Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and finely dice @red onion{1%unit}(peeled and finely diced). Dice @Roma tomato{1%unit}(diced). Zest and quarter @lime{1%unit}(zested and quartered). Mince @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(minced) leaves and stems.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the onion and cook until slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in 1 1/4 cups water, @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, @turmeric{1/4%tsp}, and @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}. Cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> For 4 servings, use 2¼ cups water and ½ tsp turmeric.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and a pinch of @chipotle powder{1%pinch} (use up to ¼ tsp if you like spicy food). Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. (TIP: Lower heat if chipotle powder is browning too quickly.) Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}.

While chicken cooks, combine tomato, cilantro, and @onion{2%tbsp} in a #medium bowl{} (taste and add more onion if desired). Squeeze in lime juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tbsp}, lime juice and zest to taste, and a pinch of @chipotle powder{1%pinch} (for an even spicier kick, use up to ¼ tsp). Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp}, half the salsa, any remaining lime zest, salt, and pepper. Divide between #bowls{}. Slice chicken crosswise; arrange over rice. Top chicken with spicy lime cream and remaining salsa. Cut any remaining lime into wedges; serve on the side.